
40. How Did You Handle API Errors in Production?
"I handle errors at 4 layers:

 Layer 1 — HTTP Interceptor
  Catches all API errors globally.
  Shows toast notification per status code.
  401 → redirect to login.
  403 → forbidden page.
  500 → server error message.

 Layer 2 — Logger Service
  Sends error details to backend.
  Includes userId, timestamp, URL.
  Only in production environment.

 Layer 3 — Global Error Handler
  Catches JavaScript errors.
  Null pointer, undefined etc.
  Navigates to error page.

 Layer 4 — Component Level
  Shows empty state or retry button.
  isLoading, error, empty states."
